12	# Timer
13	
14	A Timer component implements countdown or stopwatch functionality with start, pause,
15	resume, and reset controls. It ticks at a configurable interval and transitions to
16	a `Completed` state when a countdown reaches zero.
17	
18	```rust
19	/// Timer mode.
20	#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq, Eq, Default)]
21	pub enum Mode {
22	    /// Counts down from a target duration to zero.
23	    #[default]
24	    Countdown,
25	    /// Counts up from zero indefinitely.
26	    Stopwatch,
27	}
28	```
29	
30	## 1. State Machine
31	
32	### 1.1 States
33	
34	```rust
35	#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq, Eq)]
36	pub enum State {
37	    /// Timer is not running, at initial value.
38	    Idle,
39	    /// Timer is actively ticking.
40	    Running,
41	    /// Timer is paused, preserving current value.
42	    Paused,
43	    /// Countdown reached zero (only for Countdown mode).
44	    Completed,
45	}
46	```
47	
48	### 1.2 Events
49	
50	```rust
51	#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq, Eq)]
52	pub enum Event {
53	    /// Start or resume the timer.
54	    Start,
55	    /// Pause the timer.
56	    Pause,
57	    /// Resume from paused state.
58	    Resume,
59	    /// Reset to initial value.
60	    Reset,
61	    /// Reset to initial value and immediately start.
62	    Restart,
63	    /// A single tick interval elapsed.
64	    Tick,
65	    /// Set the remaining/elapsed time directly.
66	    SetTime(u64),
67	}
68	```
69	
70	### 1.3 Context
71	
72	```rust
73	#[derive(Clone, Debug, PartialEq)]
74	pub struct Context {
75	    /// Current time value in milliseconds.
76	    /// For countdown: remaining time. For stopwatch: elapsed time.
77	    pub current_ms: u64,
78	    /// The target duration in milliseconds (for countdown).
79	    pub target_ms: u64,
80	    /// Tick interval in milliseconds.
81	    pub interval_ms: u32,
82	    /// Timer mode.
83	    pub mode: Mode,
84	    /// Whether auto-start is enabled.
85	    pub auto_start: bool,
86	    /// Locale for internationalized messages.
87	    pub locale: Locale,
88	    /// Resolved translatable messages.
89	    pub messages: Messages,
90	    /// Component instance IDs.
91	    pub ids: ComponentIds,
92	}
93	```
94	
95	### 1.4 Props
96	
97	```rust
98	#[derive(Clone, Debug, PartialEq, HasId)]
99	pub struct Props {
100	    /// Component instance ID.
101	    pub id: String,
102	    /// Target duration in milliseconds (for countdown mode).
103	    pub target_ms: u64,
104	    /// Tick interval in milliseconds.
105	    pub interval_ms: u32,
106	    /// Timer mode (countdown or stopwatch).
107	    pub mode: Mode,
108	    /// Auto-start when mounted.
109	    pub auto_start: bool,
110	}
111	
112	impl Default for Props {
113	    fn default() -> Self {
114	        Self {
115	            id: String::new(),
116	            target_ms: 60_000,
117	            interval_ms: 1000,
118	            mode: Mode::Countdown,
119	            auto_start: false,
120	        }
121	    }
122	}
123	```
124	
125	### 1.5 Full Machine Implementation
126	
127	```rust
128	pub struct Machine;
129	
130	impl ars_core::Machine for Machine {
131	    type State = State;
132	    type Event = Event;
133	    type Context = Context;
134	    type Props = Props;
135	    type Messages = Messages;
136	    type Api<'a> = Api<'a>;
137	
138	    fn init(props: &Self::Props, env: &Env, messages: &Self::Messages) -> (Self::State, Self::Context) {
139	        let current_ms = match props.mode {
140	            Mode::Countdown => props.target_ms,
141	            Mode::Stopwatch => 0,
142	        };
143	
144	        let ids = ComponentIds::from_id(&props.id);
145	        let locale = env.locale.clone();
146	        let messages = messages.clone();
147	
148	        let state = if props.auto_start {
149	            State::Running
150	        } else {
151	            State::Idle
152	        };
153	
154	        (state, Context {
155	            current_ms,
156	            target_ms: props.target_ms,
157	            interval_ms: props.interval_ms,
158	            mode: props.mode,
159	            auto_start: props.auto_start,
160	            locale,
161	            messages,
162	            ids,
163	        })
164	    }
165	
166	    fn transition(
167	        state: &Self::State,
168	        event: &Self::Event,
169	        ctx: &Self::Context,
170	        _props: &Self::Props,
171	    ) -> Option<TransitionPlan<Self>> {
172	        match (state, event) {
173	            (State::Idle, Event::Start) => {
174	                Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Running).with_named_effect("timer-interval", |ctx, _props, send| {
175	                    let interval = ctx.interval_ms;
176	                    let timer = set_interval(interval, move || {
177	                        send(Event::Tick);
178	                    });
179	                    Box::new(move || cancel_interval(timer))
180	                }))
181	            }
182	
183	            (State::Running, Event::Tick) => {
184	                match ctx.mode {
185	                    Mode::Countdown => {
186	                        let new_ms = ctx.current_ms.saturating_sub(ctx.interval_ms as u64);
187	                        if new_ms == 0 {
188	                            Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Completed).apply(|ctx| {
189	                                ctx.current_ms = 0;
190	                            }).with_named_effect("announce", |ctx, _props, _send| {
191	                                let platform = use_platform_effects();
192	                                platform.announce(&(ctx.messages.completed_announcement)(&ctx.locale));
193	                                no_cleanup()
194	                            }))
195	                        } else {
196	                            Some(TransitionPlan::context_only(move |ctx| {
197	                                ctx.current_ms = new_ms;
198	                            }))
199	                        }
200	                    }
201	                    Mode::Stopwatch => {
202	                        let interval = ctx.interval_ms as u64;
203	                        Some(TransitionPlan::context_only(move |ctx| {
204	                            ctx.current_ms += interval;
205	                        }))
206	                    }
207	                }
208	            }
209	
210	            (State::Running, Event::Pause) => {
211	                Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Paused))
212	            }
213	
214	            (State::Paused, Event::Resume)
215	            | (State::Paused, Event::Start) => {
216	                Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Running).with_named_effect("timer-interval", |ctx, _props, send| {
217	                    let interval = ctx.interval_ms;
218	                    let timer = set_interval(interval, move || {
219	                        send(Event::Tick);
220	                    });
221	                    Box::new(move || cancel_interval(timer))
222	                }))
223	            }
224	
225	            (_, Event::Reset) => {
226	                let initial_ms = match ctx.mode {
227	                    Mode::Countdown => ctx.target_ms,
228	                    Mode::Stopwatch => 0,
229	                };
230	                Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Idle).apply(move |ctx| {
231	                    ctx.current_ms = initial_ms;
232	                }))
233	            }
234	
235	            (_, Event::Restart) => {
236	                let initial_ms = match ctx.mode {
237	                    Mode::Countdown => ctx.target_ms,
238	                    Mode::Stopwatch => 0,
239	                };
240	                Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Running).apply(move |ctx| {
241	                    ctx.current_ms = initial_ms;
242	                }).with_named_effect("timer-interval", |ctx, _props, send| {
243	                    let interval = ctx.interval_ms;
244	                    let timer = set_interval(interval, move || {
245	                        send(Event::Tick);
246	                    });
247	                    Box::new(move || cancel_interval(timer))
248	                }))
249	            }
250	
251	            (_, Event::SetTime(ms)) => {
252	                let ms = *ms;
253	                Some(TransitionPlan::context_only(move |ctx| {
254	                    ctx.current_ms = ms;
255	                }))
256	            }
257	
258	            _ => None,
259	        }
260	    }
261	
262	    fn connect<'a>(
263	        state: &'a Self::State,
264	        ctx: &'a Self::Context,
265	        props: &'a Self::Props,
266	        send: &'a dyn Fn(Self::Event),
267	    ) -> Self::Api<'a> {
268	        Api { state, ctx, props, send }
269	    }
270	}
271	```
272	
273	### 1.6 Connect / API
274	
275	```rust
276	#[derive(ComponentPart)]
277	#[scope = "timer"]
278	pub enum Part {
279	    Root,
280	    Label,
281	    Display,
282	    Progress,
283	    StartTrigger,
284	    PauseTrigger,
285	    ResetTrigger,
286	    Separator,
287	}
288	
289	pub struct Api<'a> {
290	    state: &'a State,
291	    ctx: &'a Context,
292	    props: &'a Props,
293	    send: &'a dyn Fn(Event),
294	}
295	
296	impl<'a> Api<'a> {
297	    pub fn is_running(&self) -> bool { *self.state == State::Running }
298	    pub fn is_paused(&self) -> bool { *self.state == State::Paused }
299	    pub fn is_completed(&self) -> bool { *self.state == State::Completed }
300	    pub fn is_idle(&self) -> bool { *self.state == State::Idle }
301	    pub fn current_ms(&self) -> u64 { self.ctx.current_ms }
302	
303	    /// Current time broken into hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds.
304	    pub fn display_time(&self) -> (u64, u64, u64, u64) {
305	        let ms = self.ctx.current_ms;
306	        let hours = ms / 3_600_000;
307	        let minutes = (ms % 3_600_000) / 60_000;
308	        let seconds = (ms % 60_000) / 1_000;
309	        let millis = ms % 1_000;
310	        (hours, minutes, seconds, millis)
311	    }
312	
313	    /// Progress as a fraction [0.0, 1.0] (countdown only).
314	    pub fn progress(&self) -> f64 {
315	        if self.ctx.target_ms == 0 { return 0.0; }
316	        match self.ctx.mode {
317	            Mode::Countdown => 1.0 - (self.ctx.current_ms as f64 / self.ctx.target_ms as f64),
318	            Mode::Stopwatch => self.ctx.current_ms as f64 / self.ctx.target_ms as f64,
319	        }
320	    }
321	
322	    /// Formatted time string (HH:MM:SS or MM:SS).
323	    pub fn formatted_time(&self) -> String {
324	        let (h, m, s, _) = self.display_time();
325	        if h > 0 {
326	            format!("{:02}:{:02}:{:02}", h, m, s)
327	        } else {
328	            format!("{:02}:{:02}", m, s)
329	        }
330	    }
331	
332	    fn state_str(&self) -> &'static str {
333	        match self.state {
334	            State::Idle => "idle",
335	            State::Running => "running",
336	            State::Paused => "paused",
337	            State::Completed => "completed",
338	        }
339	    }
340	
341	    pub fn root_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
342	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
343	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::Root.data_attrs();
344	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
345	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
346	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Role, "timer");
347	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Data("ars-state"), self.state_str());
348	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Live), "polite");
349	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Atomic), "true");
350	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label), self.formatted_time());
351	        attrs
352	    }
353	
354	    pub fn label_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
355	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
356	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::Label.data_attrs();
357	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
358	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
359	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Id, self.ctx.ids.part("label"));
360	        attrs
361	    }
362	
363	    pub fn display_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
364	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
365	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::Display.data_attrs();
366	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
367	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
368	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Id, self.ctx.ids.part("display"));
369	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Hidden), "true");
370	        attrs
371	    }
372	
373	    pub fn progress_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
374	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
375	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::Progress.data_attrs();
376	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
377	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
378	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Role, "progressbar");
379	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::ValueNow), format!("{:.0}", self.progress() * 100.0));
380	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::ValueMin), "0");
381	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::ValueMax), "100");
382	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label), (self.ctx.messages.progress_label)(&self.ctx.locale));
383	        attrs.set_style(CssProperty::Custom("ars-timer-progress"), format!("{:.2}", self.progress()));
384	        attrs
385	    }
386	
387	    pub fn start_trigger_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
388	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
389	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::StartTrigger.data_attrs();
390	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
391	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
392	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label), if self.is_paused() {
393	            (self.ctx.messages.resume_label)(&self.ctx.locale)
394	        } else {
395	            (self.ctx.messages.start_label)(&self.ctx.locale)
396	        });
397	        if self.is_running() || self.is_completed() {
398	            attrs.set_bool(HtmlAttr::Disabled, true);
399	        }
400	        attrs
401	    }
402	
403	    pub fn pause_trigger_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
404	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
405	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::PauseTrigger.data_attrs();
406	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
407	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
408	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label), (self.ctx.messages.pause_label)(&self.ctx.locale));
409	        if !self.is_running() {
410	            attrs.set_bool(HtmlAttr::Disabled, true);
411	        }
412	        attrs
413	    }
414	
415	    pub fn reset_trigger_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
416	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
417	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::ResetTrigger.data_attrs();
418	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
419	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
420	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label), (self.ctx.messages.reset_label)(&self.ctx.locale));
421	        if self.is_idle() {
422	            attrs.set_bool(HtmlAttr::Disabled, true);
423	        }
424	        attrs
425	    }
426	
427	    pub fn separator_attrs(&self) -> AttrMap {
428	        let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
429	        let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] = Part::Separator.data_attrs();
430	        attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
431	        attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
432	        attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Hidden), "true");
433	        attrs
434	    }
435	
436	    pub fn on_start_trigger_click(&self) {
437	        if self.is_paused() {
438	            (self.send)(Event::Resume);
439	        } else {
440	            (self.send)(Event::Start);
441	        }
442	    }
443	    pub fn on_pause_trigger_click(&self) { (self.send)(Event::Pause); }
444	    pub fn on_reset_trigger_click(&self) { (self.send)(Event::Reset); }
445	    pub fn on_restart(&self) { (self.send)(Event::Restart); }
446	}
447	
448	impl ConnectApi for Api<'_> {
449	    type Part = Part;
450	
451	    fn part_attrs(&self, part: Part) -> AttrMap {
452	        match part {
453	            Part::Root => self.root_attrs(),
454	            Part::Label => self.label_attrs(),
455	            Part::Display => self.display_attrs(),
456	            Part::Progress => self.progress_attrs(),
457	            Part::StartTrigger => self.start_trigger_attrs(),
458	            Part::PauseTrigger => self.pause_trigger_attrs(),
459	            Part::ResetTrigger => self.reset_trigger_attrs(),
460	            Part::Separator => self.separator_attrs(),
461	        }
462	    }
463	}
464	```
465	
466	## 2. Anatomy
467	
468	```text
469	Timer
470	├── Root             (required — role="timer", aria-live region)
471	├── Label            (optional — describes the timer)
472	├── Display          (required — formatted time string)
473	├── Progress         (optional — role="progressbar")
474	├── StartTrigger     (required — start/resume button)
475	├── PauseTrigger     (required — pause button)
476	├── ResetTrigger     (required — reset button)
477	└── Separator        (optional — decorative colon between time segments)
478	```
479	
480	| Part         | Element    | Key Attributes                                       |
481	| ------------ | ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
482	| Root         | `<div>`    | `role="timer"`, `aria-live="polite"`, `aria-atomic`  |
483	| Label        | `<label>`  | `id` for association                                 |
484	| Display      | `<span>`   | `aria-hidden="true"` (Root handles live region)      |
485	| Progress     | `<div>`    | `role="progressbar"`, `aria-valuenow/min/max`        |
486	| StartTrigger | `<button>` | `aria-label` (Start/Resume), `disabled` when running |
487	| PauseTrigger | `<button>` | `aria-label` (Pause), `disabled` when not running    |
488	| ResetTrigger | `<button>` | `aria-label` (Reset), `disabled` when idle           |
489	| Separator    | `<span>`   | `aria-hidden="true"` (decorative)                    |
490	
491	## 3. Accessibility
492	
493	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
494	
495	| Part         | Role          | Properties                                               |
496	| ------------ | ------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
497	| Root         | `timer`       | `aria-live="polite"`, `aria-atomic="true"`, `aria-label` |
498	| Progress     | `progressbar` | `aria-valuenow`, `aria-valuemin`, `aria-valuemax`        |
499	| StartTrigger | `button`      | `aria-label`, `disabled`                                 |
500	| PauseTrigger | `button`      | `aria-label`, `disabled`                                 |
501	| ResetTrigger | `button`      | `aria-label`, `disabled`                                 |
502	
503	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
504	
505	| Key           | Action                  |
506	| ------------- | ----------------------- |
507	| Enter / Space | Activate focused button |
508	| Tab           | Move between controls   |
509	
510	### 3.3 Screen Reader Announcements
511	
512	The Root element has `role="timer"` with `aria-live="polite"` and `aria-atomic="true"`. Time changes are announced periodically. When countdown completes, the `completed_announcement` message is announced.
513	
514	## 4. Internationalization
515	
516	### 4.1 Messages
517	
518	```rust
519	#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
520	pub struct Messages {
521	    /// Start button label. Default: `"Start timer"`.
522	    pub start_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
523	    /// Pause button label. Default: `"Pause timer"`.
524	    pub pause_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
525	    /// Reset button label. Default: `"Reset timer"`.
526	    pub reset_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
527	    /// Resume button label. Default: `"Resume timer"`.
528	    pub resume_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
529	    /// Progress bar label. Default: `"Timer progress"`.
530	    pub progress_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
531	    /// Completion announcement. Default: `"Timer completed"`.
532	    pub completed_announcement: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
533	}
534	
535	impl Default for Messages {
536	    fn default() -> Self {
537	        Self {
538	            start_label: MessageFn::static_str("Start timer"),
539	            pause_label: MessageFn::static_str("Pause timer"),
540	            reset_label: MessageFn::static_str("Reset timer"),
541	            resume_label: MessageFn::static_str("Resume timer"),
542	            progress_label: MessageFn::static_str("Timer progress"),
543	            completed_announcement: MessageFn::static_str("Timer completed"),
544	        }
545	    }
546	}
547	
548	impl ComponentMessages for Messages {}
549	```
550	
551	| Key                            | Default (en-US)     | Purpose                    |
552	| ------------------------------ | ------------------- | -------------------------- |
553	| `timer.start_label`            | `"Start timer"`     | Start button label         |
554	| `timer.resume_label`           | `"Resume timer"`    | Resume button label        |
555	| `timer.pause_label`            | `"Pause timer"`     | Pause button label         |
556	| `timer.reset_label`            | `"Reset timer"`     | Reset button label         |
557	| `timer.progress_label`         | `"Timer progress"`  | Progress bar label         |
558	| `timer.completed_announcement` | `"Timer completed"` | Screen reader announcement |
559	
560	- **Number formatting**: Time display uses locale-aware number formatting for the digits. The colon separator may vary by locale convention.
561	- **RTL**: Timer display and button layout reverse in RTL. The progress bar fills from inline-end toward inline-start.
562	
563	## 5. Library Parity
564	
565	> Compared against: Ark UI (`Timer`).
566	
567	### 5.1 Props
568	
569	| Feature            | ars-ui                       | Ark UI                | Notes                               |
570	| ------------------ | ---------------------------- | --------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
571	| `autoStart`        | `auto_start`                 | `autoStart`           | Equivalent                          |
572	| `countdown` / mode | `mode` (Countdown/Stopwatch) | `countdown` (boolean) | Equivalent (ars-ui uses enum)       |
573	| `interval`         | `interval_ms`                | `interval`            | Equivalent                          |
574	| `startMs`          | --                           | `startMs`             | Ark can start from arbitrary offset |
575	| `targetMs`         | `target_ms`                  | `targetMs`            | Equivalent                          |
576	
577	**Gaps:** None. `startMs` is niche; ars-ui can achieve via `Event::SetTime`.
578	
579	### 5.2 Anatomy
580	
581	| Part         | ars-ui                   | Ark UI                 | Notes                                               |
582	| ------------ | ------------------------ | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
583	| Root         | `Root` (role="timer")    | `Root`                 | Equivalent                                          |
584	| Label        | `Label`                  | --                     | ars-ui has label                                    |
585	| Display      | `Display`                | `Area` + `Item`        | Ark composes time segments; ars-ui has display part |
586	| Progress     | `Progress` (progressbar) | --                     | ars-ui has progress bar                             |
587	| StartTrigger | `StartTrigger`           | `ActionTrigger(start)` | Equivalent                                          |
588	| PauseTrigger | `PauseTrigger`           | `ActionTrigger(pause)` | Equivalent                                          |
589	| ResetTrigger | `ResetTrigger`           | `ActionTrigger(reset)` | Equivalent                                          |
590	| Separator    | `Separator`              | `Separator`            | Equivalent                                          |
591	| Control      | --                       | `Control`              | Ark has wrapper for action triggers                 |
592	| Item         | --                       | `Item` (per time unit) | Ark renders each unit separately                    |
593	
594	**Gaps:** None. Ark's `Item` per-unit rendering and `Control` wrapper are layout patterns the adapter handles.
595	
596	### 5.3 Events
597	
598	| Callback | ars-ui                        | Ark UI       | Notes      |
599	| -------- | ----------------------------- | ------------ | ---------- |
600	| Complete | `State::Completed` transition | `onComplete` | Equivalent |
601	| Tick     | `Event::Tick`                 | `onTick`     | Equivalent |
602	
603	**Gaps:** None.
604	
605	### 5.4 Features
606	
607	| Feature                  | ars-ui            | Ark UI         |
608	| ------------------------ | ----------------- | -------------- |
609	| Countdown mode           | Yes               | Yes            |
610	| Stopwatch mode           | Yes               | Yes            |
611	| Start/Pause/Resume/Reset | Yes               | Yes            |
612	| Restart (reset + start)  | Yes               | Yes            |
613	| Auto-start               | Yes               | Yes            |
614	| Progress indicator       | Yes (progressbar) | No             |
615	| Completion announcement  | Yes (aria-live)   | No             |
616	| Formatted time display   | Yes (HH:MM:SS)    | Yes (per-unit) |
617	
618	**Gaps:** None. ars-ui exceeds Ark UI with progress bar and SR announcements.
619	
620	### 5.5 Summary
621	
622	- **Overall:** Full parity, with additional accessibility features.
623	- **Divergences:** Ark UI renders time as individual `Item` parts per time unit (hours, minutes, seconds); ars-ui uses a single `Display` part with `formatted_time()`. ars-ui adds a `Progress` progressbar and screen reader completion announcement.
624	- **Recommended additions:** None.
625

